Introduction

NTORE, short for N-eme no Kokuhaku Renshū (Nth Time Confession Practice), is a three-member live girl group under To Hermitage. They debuted on March 27, 2022 with a live stage performance at the Idol Palette Vol.15 - NTORE debut live event in the Live Hall Prism venue in Mapo-gu, Seoul. They eventually followed up with a music debut by releasing their first mini album, Nth Time Confession Practice, on April 5, 2022.

On December 22, 2023, NTORE announced the addition of member Rua. The group's first sub-unit, HCRV, was announced on March 24, 2024. Made up of members Yui and Nara, the unit held their first performance on April 3, 2024. On October 5, 2024, it was announced that new member Byeol will be joining NTORE.

On February 14, 2025, it was announced that the group will officially disband on May 25, 2025. The contracts of Yui, Nara and Byeol will remain in place until their disbandment, whilst Liliy and Rua wouldgraduate from the group within the following months. Rua graduated from the group on February 28 while Liliy graduated on March 16.
